.TH man 1 "December 2023" "version 0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
-simple_shell / a simple shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
-shell_program / hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple-shell is a basic command-line interpreter that allows users to enter commands for execution. It provides a simple interface to the underlying operating system.

.SH OPTIONS
No command-line options are supported.

.SH COMMANDS
The simple-shell supports the following built-in commands:

.BR exit
Exit the simple-shell. If a status is provided, it will be used as the exit status.

.SH USAGE / COMPILATION
All files are to be compiled using "gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh"

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.PP
$ ./hsh
.PP
##---> /bin/ls
.PP
hsh main.c shell.c
.PP
##---> exit
.PP
$
.PP
.PP

.SH PATH
It will look inside al directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), sh(1), execve(2)

.SH BUGS
Single space required after argument.

